==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ureide
<hw>U"re*ide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Any one of the many complex derivatives of urea; thus, hydantoin,
and, in an extended dense, guanidine, caffeine, etc., are ureides.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>ureid</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-uret</ent>⟦br⟧
